# Global AI Rules for this Workspace

Before generating any code, answering questions, or making architectural decisions, you MUST read the blueprint files in the `.ai/` directory.

- `.ai/status.md`: Tracks the current state of development, phases completed, and requirement changes.
- `.ai/system-architecture.md`: Defines the microservices and their boundaries.
- `.ai/tech-stack.md`: Defines allowed languages (Go) and environment variables.
- `.ai/schemas.md`: Defines database DDLs, schemas, and API contracts.
- `.ai/common-rules.md`: Defines workflow, scaffolding, and quality requirements.

You must follow these constraints strictly. Do not hallucinate different stack choices or architecture designs.
